=You are an expert evaluator of AI-generated n8n workflow error diagnoses.
You will receive a diagnosis generated by another AI agent. Your job is to
independently evaluate the quality of that diagnosis and validate or correct
the confidence score.

DIAGNOSIS TO EVALUATE:
direct_cause: {{ $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.direct_cause }}
underlying_cause: {{ $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.underlying_cause }}
timing_analysis: {{ $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.timing_analysis }}
fix: {{ JSON.stringify($('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.fix) }}
prevention: {{ $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.prevention }}
error_type: {{ $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.error_type }}
self_reported_confidence: {{ $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.confidence }}
is_recurring: {{ $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output.is_recurring }}

ORIGINAL ERROR CONTEXT:
Workflow name: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.workflow_name }}
Error message: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_message }}
Failing node name: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_node.name }}
Failing node type: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_node.type }}
Failing node parameters: {{ JSON.stringify($('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_node.parameters) }}
Business action: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.business_context.business_action }}
Historical context: ={{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.historical_context.filter(h => h.direct_cause !== null).length > 0 ? JSON.stringify($('Code - Prepare context').first().json.historical_context.filter(h => h.direct_cause !== null)) : 'No historical data available.' }}

EVALUATION RUBRIC — score each criterion yes or no:
1. Is the direct_cause specific (not generic like "the node failed")?
2. Is the underlying_cause different from the direct_cause and more insightful?
3. Does the error_type correctly match the described cause?
4. Is the self_reported_confidence realistic given the available context?

Respond with valid JSON only. No markdown. No explanation. No code fences.
Use this exact structure:
{
  "validated_confidence": 0-100,
  "confidence_adjustment_reason": "one sentence explaining why you adjusted or kept the confidence score"
}

Rules for validated_confidence:
- If all 4 criteria pass: increase self_reported_confidence by max 5 points
- If 3 criteria pass: keep self_reported_confidence unchanged
- If 2 criteria pass: lower self_reported_confidence by 10-15 points
- If 1 criterion passes: lower self_reported_confidence by 15-25 points
- Never set validated_confidence above 95

=SECTION 1 — ROLE
You analyze failures in automated n8n business workflows.
Your task is NOT to describe the technical error.
Your task is to reason about WHY this workflow failed.
Always distinguish: direct cause, underlying cause, timing reason.

SECTION 2 — BUSINESS CONTEXT
Workflow name: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.workflow_name }}
Failing node: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_node.name }} 
  (type: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_node.type }} 
  v{{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_node.typeVersion }})
Last successful node: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.lastNodeExecuted }}
Error message: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_message }}
Error name: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_name }}
Error context: {{ JSON.stringify($('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_context) }}
Additional error messages: {{ JSON.stringify($('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_messages) }}
Node parameters: {{ JSON.stringify($('Code - Prepare context').first().json.error_node.parameters) }}
Execution URL: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.execution_url }}
Business action: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.business_context.business_action }}
Success looks like: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.business_context.success_looks_like }}
Known failure modes: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.business_context.known_failure_modes }}
Run frequency: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.business_context.run_frequency }}
External dependencies: {{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.business_context.external_dependencies }}

SECTION 3 — WORKFLOW STRUCTURE
{{ JSON.stringify($('Code - Prepare context').first().json.workflow_json) }}

SECTION 4 — HISTORICAL CONTEXT
If historical diagnoses are present below, use them to identify recurring patterns.
Note if the same error_type or direct_cause appears multiple times.
={{ $('Code - Prepare context').first().json.historical_context.filter(h => h.direct_cause !== null).length > 0 
  ? JSON.stringify($('Code - Prepare context').first().json.historical_context.filter(h => h.direct_cause !== null))
  : 'No historical data available for this workflow.' }}

SECTION 5 — OUTPUT INSTRUCTION
Respond with valid JSON only. No markdown. No explanation. No code fences.
Use this exact structure:
{
  "direct_cause": "specific technical reason the node failed",
  "underlying_cause": "root cause behind the direct cause",
  "timing_analysis": "why this happened now vs other times",
  "fix": "1. First step starting with a verb. 2. Second step starting with a verb. 3. Third step starting with a verb.",
  "prevention": "how to prevent this in future",
  "error_type": "auth|network|data|logic|rate_limit|config",
  "confidence": 0-100,
  "is_recurring": true ONLY if BOTH the same error_type AND a highly similar direct_cause appear in historical context. If only the error_type matches but the direct_cause is different, set to false
}

Fix must be a single string with maximum 3 numbered steps.
Each step must start with a verb and be understandable for a non-technical business owner.

Provide your raw honest confidence score (0-100) based purely on how well
the available data supports your diagnosis. Do not overthink this — the
score will be independently validated.

parameters.jsCode:
const webhook = $('Code - Build context').first().json;
const workflow_id = webhook.workflow_id ?? null;
const workflow_name = webhook.workflow_name ?? null;
const error_message = webhook.error_message ?? null;
const error_name = webhook.error_name ?? null;
const error_description = webhook.error_description ?? null;
const error_stack = webhook.error_stack ?? null;
const error_messages = Array.isArray(webhook.error_messages) ? webhook.error_messages : [];
const error_context = (webhook.error_context && typeof webhook.error_context === 'object') ? webhook.error_context : {};
const error_node = (webhook.error_node && typeof webhook.error_node === 'object') ? webhook.error_node : { name: null, type: null, typeVersion: null, parameters: {} };
const lastNodeExecuted = webhook.lastNodeExecuted ?? null;
const execution_id = webhook.execution_id ?? null;
const execution_mode = webhook.execution_mode ?? null;
const execution_url = webhook.execution_url ?? null;
const business_context = (webhook.business_context && typeof webhook.business_context === 'object') ? webhook.business_context : {};
const workflow_json = webhook.workflow_json ?? null;
const technical_email = webhook.technical_email ?? null;
const from_email = webhook.from_email ?? null;

let historical_context = [];
try {
  const supabaseItems = $('Supabase - Get historical context').all();
  if (Array.isArray(supabaseItems) && supabaseItems.length > 0) {
    historical_context = supabaseItems
      .filter(item => item && item.json)
      .map(item => ({
        created_at: item.json.created_at ?? null,
        direct_cause: item.json.direct_cause ?? null,
        underlying_cause: item.json.underlying_cause ?? null,
        error_type: item.json.error_type ?? null,
        validated_confidence: item.json.validated_confidence ?? null,
        is_recurring: item.json.is_recurring ?? null,
        error_message: item.json.error_message ?? null,
        fix: item.json.fix ?? null,
      }))
      .sort((a, b) => new Date(b.created_at) - new Date(a.created_at))
      .slice(0, 3);
  }
} catch (e) {
  historical_context = [];
}

return [{
  json: {
    workflow_id,
    workflow_name,
    error_message,
    error_name,
    error_description,
    error_stack,
    error_messages,
    error_context,
    error_node,
    lastNodeExecuted,
    execution_id,
    execution_mode,
    execution_url,
    business_context,
    workflow_json,
    technical_email,
    from_email,
    historical_context
  }
}];

const diagnosis = $('Claude Diagnosis').first().json.output;
const scoring = $('Claude Scoring Judge').first().json.output;
const context = $('Code - Prepare context').first().json;

const raw_validated = scoring.validated_confidence ?? 0;
const validated_confidence = Math.min(100, Math.max(0, raw_validated));

return [{
  json: {
    direct_cause: diagnosis.direct_cause,
    underlying_cause: diagnosis.underlying_cause,
    timing_analysis: diagnosis.timing_analysis,
    fix: diagnosis.fix,
    prevention: diagnosis.prevention,
    error_type: diagnosis.error_type,
    is_recurring: diagnosis.is_recurring,
    self_reported_confidence: diagnosis.confidence,
    validated_confidence: validated_confidence,
    confidence_adjustment_reason: scoring.confidence_adjustment_reason,
    technical_email: context.technical_email,
    from_email: context.from_email,
    workflow_id: context.workflow_id,
    workflow_name: context.workflow_name,
    error_message: context.error_message,
    error_node: context.error_node,
    execution_id: context.execution_id,
    execution_mode: context.execution_mode,
    execution_url: context.execution_url,
    lastNodeExecuted: context.lastNodeExecuted,
    error_stack: context.error_stack,
    business_context: context.business_context
  }
}];

const errorData = $('Error Trigger').first().json;
const configData = $('Config - context').first().json;
const error = errorData?.execution?.error || {};
const execution = errorData?.execution || {};
const workflow = errorData?.workflow || {};

// Collect all workflow_ fields and merge into one array
const allWorkflows = [];
for (const key of Object.keys(configData)) {
  if (key.startsWith('workflow_')) {
    try {
      const parsed = JSON.parse(configData[key]);
      if (Array.isArray(parsed)) {
        allWorkflows.push(...parsed);
      }
    } catch (e) {}
  }
}

const workflowId = String(workflow.id || '');
const match = allWorkflows.find(w => String(w.workflow_id) === workflowId) || {};

const business_context = {
  business_action: match.business_action || '',
  success_looks_like: match.success_looks_like || '',
  known_failure_modes: match.known_failure_modes || '',
  run_frequency: match.run_frequency || '',
  external_dependencies: match.external_dependencies || ''
};

return [{
  json: {
    error_message: error.message || '',
    error_name: error.name || '',
    error_description: error.description || '',
    error_stack: error.stack || '',
    error_messages: Array.isArray(error.messages) ? error.messages : [],
    error_context: (error.context && typeof error.context === 'object') ? error.context : {},
    error_node: (error.node && typeof error.node === 'object') ? error.node : {},
    last_node_executed: execution.lastNodeExecuted || '',
    execution_id: execution.id || '',
    execution_mode: execution.mode || '',
    execution_url: execution.url || '',
    workflow_id: workflowId,
    workflow_name: workflow.name || '',
    business_context,
    technical_email: configData.technical_email || '',
    from_email: configData.from_email || ''
  }
}];

